<Base title="Objects of Intention" description="The principles for future Dunhuang Within jewelry, journals, and symbolic objects: traceable sources, cultural context, practice, and no false claims."><article class="article"><nav class="breadcrumbs"><a href="/">Home</a> / Objects</nav><p class="eyebrow">Future layer · principles first</p><h1>Objects of Intention</h1><p class="lede">Carry the path. Not a cure.</p><p>Dunhuang Within does not sell objects yet. This space defines the standard future jewelry, journals, and symbolic pieces must meet before they appear.</p><h2>Every object begins with four questions.</h2><ol><li><strong>What is the documented source?</strong> A mural, manuscript, landscape, material tradition, or responsibly researched symbol.</li><li><strong>What can we responsibly say?</strong> Historical context is separated from contemporary reflection.</li><li><strong>What practice does it support?</strong> A breath, question, walk, ritual of attention, or boundary around noise.</li><li><strong>Who and what made it?</strong> Material, maker, process, provenance, and any religious relationship are described accurately.</li></ol><h2>What an object may carry</h2><p>A wish for courage. A reminder to return. A symbol of compassion. A private vow. The memory of a chosen path.</p><h2>What it will never promise</h2><p>No treatment of disease. No guaranteed fortune. No invented ancient ritual. No “Dunhuang energy” presented as a measurable fact. No item described as blessed or consecrated without a real, documented process and consent.</p><h2>Future families</h2><div class="needs-list"><div class="need-row"><strong>Desert Crossing</strong><span>Objects for courage and transition</span><span>Future</span></div><div class="need-row"><strong>Hidden Cave</strong><span>Objects for silence and reflection</span><span>Future</span></div><div class="need-row"><strong>Oasis Return</strong><span>Objects for enoughness and renewal</span><span>Future</span></div><div class="need-row"><strong>Silk Road</strong><span>Objects for direction and connection</span><span>Future</span></div></div><div class="actions"><a class="button" href="/find-your-path/">Find Your Path</a><a class="button secondary" href="/symbols/">Explore Symbols</a></div></article></Base>
